p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The exis</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ting Charter has been shown to split responsibility between the BBC Trust and the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">E</span><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">xecutive which is NOT good and has in part been responsible for much of the alleged BBC </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">xcesses. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Thus a new charter must give a greater clarity and perhaps a slightly heav</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ier touch monitoring of operational management whilst still being an arm’s length controlling body. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">There is a place for the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Trust</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">preserve</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> the public interest and to ensure </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">clearly</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">visible</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">independence</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> from </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Political</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> or </span><span style="font-family:Calibr